# PMI-ACP (Agile)
###### Apologies this page needs to be cleaned up

Characteristics of Projects

 - Are time oriented

 - Unique

 - Offer a deliverable

Negative risks threats can be seen as "anti-value"

Anti-Value: factors that have the potential to erode, remove or reduce value if they occur

MoSCoW: Must have, Should have, Could have, Would like to have, but not this time.

Simple schemes : label items priority 1 and 2 etc

Monopoly money: Distribute monopoly money equal to the amount of the project budget and distribute funds among system features.

100 point method: each stakeholder is given 100 points to vote for the most important requirements.

Principles of stakeholder engagement

-   get the right stakeholders
-   cement stakeholders involvement
-   actively manage stakeholder interest
-   frequently discuss what "done" looks like
-   Show progress and capabilities
-   Candidly discuss estimates and projections

High Performing teams are:

-   Self-organizing
-   Empowered
-    Can Solve any problem
-   Committed to team success
-   Owns its decisions and commitments
-   Motivated by trust
-   Consensus-Driven
-   Constructive disagreement

Progressive Elaboration

Rolling wave planning - planning at multiple points in time as more information about the project becomes available.

Progressive elaboration is what we do to incorporate new information into our plans.

Value-Based Analysis

Value-based decomposition is a continuation of the process of value-based analysis

Timeboxing - short, fixed duration period in which a defined set of activities or work is undertaken.
